      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are intended to protect domestic industries by making imported goods more expensive, theoretically allowing local businesses to compete better. However, this protection often raises prices for consumers, as the cost of the tariff is frequently passed down to the buyer. Furthermore, tariffs can provoke retaliatory tariffs from other countries, harming domestic exporters as well. Ultimately, the impact depends heavily on the specific industry and global trade dynamics.",
