      "content": "You are highlighting a core debate between economic theory and national policy goals. While free trade promotes efficiency by allowing resources to go where they are most cost-effective, this efficiency often coincides with corporate maximization of profit through outsourcing. Prioritizing domestic labor is a valid political and social goal, but policymakers must balance that with the realities of global market pressures. The \"soundest\" policy often depends on which set of priorities—worker stability or market efficiency—a government chooses to emphasize.",
